                <note type="updated" update="title" import="tengyur-data-3824-3980_PH_new_v2.4.xml" date-time="2021-11-02T14:13:45.147Z" user="admin">The Tibetan sbyang and Sanskrit pariṣkāra can mean either “purifying” or “preparing/cultivating.” Since the object of the verb is “ground” (bhūmi; sa),
